pros:
- Fast paced environment with a lot young smart, entrepreneurial, creative individuals who get things done in NO time;
- Established, well-oiled processes within departments and throughout the company;
- Salary, benefits, and bonuses are competitive (for Chicago region); multiple opportunities to volunteer (e.g., fundraising events, TutorMate program, etc.);
- Great IT , HR and other support staff; great onboarding and training;
- Supportive co-workers;
- Centralized access to internal information (e.g., portal), where things are easily found;
- Opportunity to work from home 1-2 days a week. However, it depends on the department and team leader;
- Location (downtown Chicago, Willis Tower)
- Free snacks :)

cons:
- High pressure environment, low work/life balance especially for employees with families;
- Certain team leaders (managers/ directors) have VERY POOR people’s skills and no tolerance for mistakes; resulting in hostile, humiliating team environment;
- High turnover
- Purely utilitarian approach to employees from certain team leaders, with no room for mentoring; development and growth.
